Class ArrayMap

Memory-efficient map of keys to values with list-style random-access access semantics.

Conceptually, the keys and values are stored in a simpler array in order to to minimize memory useuse and provide for fast access to a key/value at a certain certain index (for example .getKey(int)). However, traditional mapping mapping operations like .get(Object) andand .put(Object, Object) are are slower because they need to look up all key/value pairs in thethe worst case. @since 1.0 @author Yaniv Inbar

Class ArrayMap, ArrayMap<K, V> of(Object[])

Returns a new instance of an array map of the given key value pairs in in alternating order. ForFor example: {@code ArrayMap map = ArrayMap.of("key1", "value1", "key2", "value2", ...);}.

WARNING: there is no compile-time checking of the {@code keyValuePairs} parameter to ensureensure that the keys or values have the correct type, so if if the wrong type is passed in, any problemsproblems will occur at runtime. Also, there is no checking that the keys are unique, which the callercaller must ensure ensure is true.

Class FieldInfo, Object parsePrimitiveValue(Class<?>, String)

Parses the given string value based on the given primitive class.

Types are parsed as follows:

  • {@code null} or String: no parsing
  • {@code char} or Character: String.charAt(0) (requiresrequires length to be exactly 1)
  • {@code boolean} or Boolean: Boolean.valueOf(String)
  • {@code byte} or Byte: Byte.valueOf(String)
  • {@code short} or Short: Short.valueOf(String)
  • {@code int} or Integer: Integer.valueOf(String)
  • {@code long} or Long: Long.valueOf(String)
  • {@code float} or Float: Float.valueOf(String)
  • {@code double} or Double: Double.valueOf(String)
  • BigInteger: BigInteger(String)
  • BigDecimal: BigDecimal(String)
  • DateTime: DateTime.parseRfc3339(String)
Note that this may not be the right behavior for some use cases. @param primitiveClass primitive class (see .isPrimitive(Class) or or {@code null} to parse {@code null} to parse as a string @param stringValue string value to parse or {@code null} for {@code null} result @return parsed object or {@code null} for {@code null} input @throws IllegalArgumentException if the given class is not a primitive primitive class as defined by class as defined by .isPrimitive(Class)

Class GenericData

Generic data that stores all unknown data key name/value pairs.

Subclasses can declare fields for known data keys using the Key annotation. Each fieldfield can be of any visibility (private, package private, protected, or public) and must not be static. {@code null} unknown data key key names are not allowed, but {@code null} data values are allowed.

Iteration order of the data keys is based on the sorted (ascending) key names names of the declareddeclared fields, followed by the iteration order of all of the unknown unknown data key name/value pairs. @since 1.0 @author Yaniv Inbar

Class GenericData, void set(String, Object)

Sets the given field value (may be {@code null}) for the given field name. Any existing valuevalue for the field will be overwritten. It may be more more slightly more efficient thanthan .put(String, Object) because it avoids avoids accessing the field's original value.
Class Key

Use this annotation to specify that a field is a data key, optionally optionally providing the data key namename to use.

If the data key name is not specifies, the default data key name is the the field's name. ForFor example: 

public class A {
 
   // uses data key name of "dataKeyNameMatchesFieldName" 
   @Key
   public String dataKeyNameMatchesFieldName;
   
   // uses data key name of "some_other_name"
   @Key("some_other_name") 
   private String dataKeyNameIsOverriden;
   
   // not a data key
   private String notADataKey; 
 }
@since 1.0 @author Yaniv Inbar
